For Question 1:  Here is O(N*logM) using TreeSet
Create a TreeSet of `B` // time: O(MlongM)
Iterate `A` and get ceiling of `A-d`, If ceiling is not found or found& greater than `A+d` then this should be accounted for answer.

```
import java.util.*;
public class HelloWorld{
     public static void main(String []args){

         int []A ={2,9,19, 20};
         int []B ={16, 13,8};
         int c = process(A, B, 3);
        System.out.println("count: "+c);
     }
    private static int process(int [] A, int [] B, int d){
        TreeSet<Integer> bTS = new TreeSet<>();
        for(int b:B){
            bTS.add(b);
        }

        int count = 0;
        for(int a:A){
            int aMin = a-d;
            Integer bMin = bTS.ceiling(aMin);
            if(null == bMin || bMin>(a+d) ){
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
